h3cEOCCommon.name: h3cEOCCommon
h3cEOCCommon.contactinfo: SMB EOC Team H3C Technologies Co., Ltd. 310 Liuhe Road, Zhijiang Science Park, Hangzhou, P.R.China http://www.h3c.com Zip:310053.
h3cEOCCommon.description: The objects in this MIB module are used to manage and display common configuration between Ethernet Passive Optical Network (EOC) port which are based on the Ethernet in the First Mile (EFM) Passive Optical Network(PON) as defined in IEEE Draft P802.3ah/D3.0 clause 60, 64, 65.. and Ethernet Over Cable (EOC) which is based on HomePlug AV Specification.

h3cEOCCommonSysVersion.name: h3cEOCCommonSysVersion
h3cEOCCommonSysVersion.description: Eoc version. If the object length is zero, it means the version is unknown. The length is up to 1024.

h3cEOCCommonUpLinkMacAddress.name: h3cEOCCommonUpLinkMacAddress
h3cEOCCommonUpLinkMacAddress.description: EOC CLT's uplink device's mac address.

h3cEOCCommonCltManTable.name: h3cEOCCommonCltManTable
h3cEOCCommonCltManTable.description: This table defines the primary parameters of the CLT configuration.

h3cEOCCommonCltManEntry.name: h3cEOCCommonCltManEntry
h3cEOCCommonCltManEntry.description: The entry of the table h3cEOCCommonCltManTable.

h3cEOCCommonCltAutoAuthorize.name: h3cEOCCommonCltAutoAuthorize
h3cEOCCommonCltAutoAuthorize.description: This value determines whether software performs self-authorization for each Cable Network Unit(CNU) registering to the network. Setting it to false means for every CNU registering, software requires external authorization, and until it's done the CNU is not authenticated. True value means software authorizes each CNU registering to the network automatically.

h3cEOCCommonCltMaxAllowToAccess.name: h3cEOCCommonCltMaxAllowToAccess
h3cEOCCommonCltMaxAllowToAccess.description: This value determines how many CNU can be bound in this CLT. If the number of CNU is more than this value , then the rest of CNU should not be allow to access.

h3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBWMinVal.name: h3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBWMinVal
h3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBWMinVal.description: The lower limit of total-bandwidth which is confined to h3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBW.

h3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBWMaxVal.name: h3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBWMaxVal
h3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBWMaxVal.description: The upper limit of total-bandwidth which is confined to h3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBW.

h3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBWMinVal.name: h3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBWMinVal
h3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBWMinVal.description: The lower limit of high priority bandwidth which is confined to h3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBW.

h3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBWMaxVal.name: h3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBWMaxVal
h3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBWMaxVal.description: The upper limit of high priority bandwidth which is confined to h3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBW.

h3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBWMinVal.name: h3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBWMinVal
h3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBWMinVal.description: The lower limit of total-bandwidth which is confined to h3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBW.

h3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBWMaxVal.name: h3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBWMaxVal
h3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBWMaxVal.description: The upper limit of total-bandwidth which is confined to h3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBW.

h3cEOCComCnuAttenThrA.name: h3cEOCComCnuAttenThrA
h3cEOCComCnuAttenThrA.description: The value of cnu's average attenuation good level thresholds.

h3cEOCComCnuAttenThrB.name: h3cEOCComCnuAttenThrB
h3cEOCComCnuAttenThrB.description: The value of cnu's average attenuation normal level thresholds.

h3cEOCComCnuRateDropThr.name: h3cEOCComCnuRateDropThr
h3cEOCComCnuRateDropThr.description: The value of cnu's Tx/Rx rate drop thresholds.

h3cEOCComCnuSysManTable.name: h3cEOCComCnuSysManTable
h3cEOCComCnuSysManTable.description: This table implements the management of CNUs(Coax Network Unit).

h3cEOCComCnuSysManEntry.name: h3cEOCComCnuSysManEntry
h3cEOCComCnuSysManEntry.description: The entry of the table h3cEOCComCnuSysManTable.

h3cEOCComCnuCableIfindex.name: h3cEOCComCnuCableIfindex
h3cEOCComCnuCableIfindex.description: The index of cable port which uniquely identifies the cable port of one device.

h3cEOCComCnuDeviceType.name: h3cEOCComCnuDeviceType
h3cEOCComCnuDeviceType.description: The type of the EOC CNU(Coax Network Unit).

h3cEOCComCnuDeviceAlias.name: h3cEOCComCnuDeviceAlias
h3cEOCComCnuDeviceAlias.description: EOC CNU's alias which display as the device's name, it's recommended to set it uniquely and understandably.

h3cEOCComCnuDescr.name: h3cEOCComCnuDescr
h3cEOCComCnuDescr.description: User's description, including user's address, name, telephone number and so on.

h3cEOCComCnuUpTime.name: h3cEOCComCnuUpTime
h3cEOCComCnuUpTime.description: The time since the CNU last registered to the network.

h3cEOCComCnuVLANType.name: h3cEOCComCnuVLANType
h3cEOCComCnuVLANType.description: port vlan types. hybrid (3) port can carry multiple VLANs. If fabric function is supported, fabric(4) means the port is a fabric port.

h3cEOCComCnuPvid.name: h3cEOCComCnuPvid
h3cEOCComCnuPvid.description: The PVID, the VLAN ID assigned to untagged frames or Priority-Tagged frames received on cable interface.

h3cEOCComCnuVlanTag.name: h3cEOCComCnuVlanTag
h3cEOCComCnuVlanTag.description: VLAN is set tagged or untagged on cable interface.

h3cEOCComCnuReset.name: h3cEOCComCnuReset
h3cEOCComCnuReset.description: This variable is used to reset the CNU device. The interface may be unavailable while the reset occurs and data may be lost. During reading operation it returns the state of the CNU device. running(1) indicates and operates normal operation, reset(2) indicates and operates reset mode. Writing can be done all the time.

h3cEOCComCnuSave.name: h3cEOCComCnuSave
h3cEOCComCnuSave.description: Save the UNI and CNU related configurations to the CNU.

h3cEOCComCnuAccess.name: h3cEOCComCnuAccess
h3cEOCComCnuAccess.description: Control whether the user can access to the network.

h3cEOCComCnuMacTable.name: h3cEOCComCnuMacTable
h3cEOCComCnuMacTable.description: This table implements the management of CNUs.

h3cEOCComCnuMacEntry.name: h3cEOCComCnuMacEntry
h3cEOCComCnuMacEntry.description: The entry of the table h3cEOCComCnuMacTable.

h3cEOCComCnuInfoTable.name: h3cEOCComCnuInfoTable
h3cEOCComCnuInfoTable.description: Primary status of the specified CNU. There will be one row in this table for each information in the system.

h3cEOCComCnuHardwareVersion.name: h3cEOCComCnuHardwareVersion
h3cEOCComCnuHardwareVersion.description: EOC CNU's hardware version. If the object length is zero, it means the version is unknown.

h3cEOCComCnuLinkState.name: h3cEOCComCnuLinkState
h3cEOCComCnuLinkState.description: The cable port's link state. The physicaldown(1) state indicates that the CNU is not powered on. The linkdown(2) state indicates that the CNU is powered on, but registers fail. The linkup(3) state indicates that the CNU is powered on, and registers successful.

h3cEOCComCnuSoftwareVersion.name: h3cEOCComCnuSoftwareVersion
h3cEOCComCnuSoftwareVersion.description: EOC CNU's software version. If the object length is zero, it means the version is unknown.

h3cEOCComCnuTxRate.name: h3cEOCComCnuTxRate
h3cEOCComCnuTxRate.description: The cnu's capability of tx speed in unit of 1Mbps.

h3cEOCComCnuRxRate.name: h3cEOCComCnuRxRate
h3cEOCComCnuRxRate.description: The cnu's capability of rx speed in unit of 1Mbps.

h3cEOCComCnuTxRateDrop.name: h3cEOCComCnuTxRateDrop
h3cEOCComCnuTxRateDrop.description: The cnu's capability droping of tx speed from it's history max value in unit of %.

h3cEOCComCnuRxRateDrop.name: h3cEOCComCnuRxRateDrop
h3cEOCComCnuRxRateDrop.description: The cnu's capability droping of rx speed from it's history max value in unit of %.

h3cEOCComCnuBandWidthEntry.name: h3cEOCComCnuBandWidthEntry
h3cEOCComCnuBandWidthEntry.description: The entry of table h3cEOCComCnuBandWidthTable. It is a pre-configuration.

h3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBW.name: h3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBW
h3cEOCComCnuMaxDownBW.description: Maximum bandwidth allowed for the CNU, measured in Kbit/s.

h3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBW.name: h3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBW
h3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBW.description: High priority bandwidth - measured in Kbit/s. The value of this object should be the multiple of the value of h3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBW. The high priority bandwidth should not be larger than the maximum bandwidth.

h3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBW.name: h3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBW
h3cEOCComCnuMaxUpBW.description: Total bandwidth - measured in Kbit/s. The value of this object should be the multiple of the value of h3cEOCComCnuSlaHighPriBW. The total bandwidth should be larger than the high priority bandwidth.

h3cEOCComUniManTable.name: h3cEOCComUniManTable
h3cEOCComUniManTable.description: This table defines several user network interface(UNI) system parameters.

h3cEOCUniIndex.name: h3cEOCUniIndex
h3cEOCUniIndex.description: The index value which uniquely identifies the FE(Fast Ethernet) interface of the CNU.

h3cEOCComUniDescr.name: h3cEOCComUniDescr
h3cEOCComUniDescr.description: A textual string containing information about the interface. This string should include the name of the manufacturer, the product name and the version of the interface hardware and software.

h3cEOCComUniStatus.name: h3cEOCComUniStatus
h3cEOCComUniStatus.description: The desired state of the user network interface. When a managed system initializes, all user network interfaces start with down state. The testing state indicates that no operational packets can be passed. As a result of either explicit management action or per configuration information retained by the managed system, h3cEOCComUniStatus is then changed to either the up or testing states (or remains in the down state).

h3cEOCComUniCurrentSpeed.name: h3cEOCComUniCurrentSpeed
h3cEOCComUniCurrentSpeed.description: An estimate of the interface's current bandwidth in bits per second. For interfaces which do not vary in bandwidth or for those where no accurate estimation can be made, this object should contain the nominal bandwidth. If the bandwidth of the interface is greater than the maximum value reportable by this object then this object should report its maximum value (4,294,967,295). For a sub-layer which has no concept of bandwidth, this object should be zero.

h3cEOCComUniCurrentDuplex.name: h3cEOCComUniCurrentDuplex
h3cEOCComUniCurrentDuplex.description: The current mode of operation of the MAC entity. 'unknown' indicates that the current duplex mode could not be determined. Management control of the duplex mode is accomplished through the MAU MIB. When an interface does not support autonegotiation, or when autonegotiation is not enabled, the duplex mode is controlled using ifMauDefaultType. When autonegotiation is supported and enabled, duplex mode is controlled using ifMauAutoNegAdvertisedBits. In either case, the currently operating duplex mode is reflected both in this object and in ifMauType. Note that this object provides redundant information with ifMauType. Normally, redundant objects are discouraged. However, in this instance, it allows a management application to determine the duplex status of an interface without having to know every possible value of ifMauType. This was felt to be sufficiently valuable to justify the redundancy.

h3cEOCComUniMdi.name: h3cEOCComUniMdi
h3cEOCComUniMdi.description: Type of the line connected to UNI interface: mdi-ii(straight-through cable), mdi-x (crossover cable), mdi-auto (auto-sensing).

h3cEOCComUniFlowControl.name: h3cEOCComUniFlowControl
h3cEOCComUniFlowControl.description: Flow control status. true(1) - Flow control status enable. false(2) - Flow control status disable.

h3cEOCComUniCountReset.name: h3cEOCComUniCountReset
h3cEOCComUniCountReset.description: Reset the counter which is about packets of the interface, then the counter will change to zero. There is no sense in reading this object.

h3cEOCComUniAlias.name: h3cEOCComUniAlias
h3cEOCComUniAlias.description: This object is an 'alias' name for the interface as specified by a network manager, and provides a non- volatile 'handle' for the interface. On the first instantiation of an interface, the value of h3cEOCComUniAlias associated with that interface is the zero-length string. As and when a value is written into an instance of h3cEOCComUniAlias through a network management set operation, then the agent must retain the supplied value in the h3cEOCComUniAlias instance associated with the same interface for as long as that interface remains instantiated, including across all re- initializations/reboots of the network management system, including those which result in a change of the interface's ifIndex and h3cEOCUniIndex value. An example of the value which a network manager might store in this object for a WAN interface is the (Telco's) circuit number/identifier of the interface. Some agents may support write-access only for interfaces having particular values of h3cEOCComUniType. An agent which supports write access to this object is required to keep the value in non-volatile storage, but it may limit the length of new values depending on how much storage is already occupied by the current values for other interfaces.

h3cEOCComUniType.name: h3cEOCComUniType
h3cEOCComUniType.description: The type of interface. Additional values for h3cEOCComUniType are assigned by the Internet Assigned Numbers Authority(IANA), through updating the syntax of the IANAifType textual convention.

h3cEOCComUniVLANType.name: h3cEOCComUniVLANType
h3cEOCComUniVLANType.description: port vlan types. hybrid (3) port can carry multiple VLANs. If fabric function is supported, fabric(4) means the port is a fabric port.

h3cEOCComUniPvid.name: h3cEOCComUniPvid
h3cEOCComUniPvid.description: The PVID, the VLAN ID assigned to untagged frames or Priority-Tagged frames received on this port.

h3cEOCComUniVlanTag.name: h3cEOCComUniVlanTag
h3cEOCComUniVlanTag.description: VLAN is set tagged or untagged.

h3cEOCComUniPriority.name: h3cEOCComUniPriority
h3cEOCComUniPriority.description: The default ingress User Priority for this port. This only has effect on media, such as Ethernet, that do not support native User Priority.

h3cEOCComUniUpLineRate.name: h3cEOCComUniUpLineRate
h3cEOCComUniUpLineRate.description: The max speed upload in units of 1,000 bits per second on this interface. The value should between 0 and 100Mbps. If the value is 0, it means that the upload speed is only restricted by the physical line.

h3cEOCComUniDownLineRate.name: h3cEOCComUniDownLineRate
h3cEOCComUniDownLineRate.description: The max speed download in units of 1,000 bits per second on this interface. The value should between 0 and 100Mbps. If the value is 0, it means that the download speed is only restricted by the physical line.

h3cEOCComUniAdminStatus.name: h3cEOCComUniAdminStatus
h3cEOCComUniAdminStatus.description: Control if open or close the UNI. If choose up(1), means the UNI is opened and packets can pass it. If choose down(2), means the UNI is closed and all packets will be discard.

h3cEOCComUniCountTable.name: h3cEOCComUniCountTable
h3cEOCComUniCountTable.description: A list of interface counter about frames entries.

h3cEOCComUniCountEntry.name: h3cEOCComUniCountEntry
h3cEOCComUniCountEntry.description: An entry containing management information applicable to a particular interface.

h3cEOCUniInPkts.name: h3cEOCUniInPkts
h3cEOCUniInPkts.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets, broadcast packets, and multicast packets) received.

h3cEOCUniInUPkts.name: h3cEOCUniInUPkts
h3cEOCUniInUPkts.description: The total number of good packets received that are directed to the unicast address. Note that this does not include multicast and broadcast packets.

h3cEOCUniInBPkts.name: h3cEOCUniInBPkts
h3cEOCUniInBPkts.description: The total number of good packets received that are directed to the broadcast address. Note that this does not include multicast packets.

h3cEOCUniInMPkts.name: h3cEOCUniInMPkts
h3cEOCUniInMPkts.description: The total number of good packets received that are directed to a multicast address. Note that this number does not include packets directed to the broadcast address.

h3cEOCUniInPausePkts.name: h3cEOCUniInPausePkts
h3cEOCUniInPausePkts.description: A count of MAC Control packets received on this interface by the pause(flow control) operation. This counter does not increment when the interface is in a half-duplex mode. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system.

h3cEOCUniInTotalErrors.name: h3cEOCUniInTotalErrors
h3cEOCUniInTotalErrors.description: Total count of the error packets received on this interface.

h3cEOCUniInCRCErrs.name: h3cEOCUniInCRCErrs
h3cEOCUniInCRCErrs.description: The total number of packets received that had a length (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) of between 64 and 1518 octets, inclusive, but had either a bad Frame Check Sequence (FCS) with an integral number of octets (FCS Error) or a bad FCS with a non-integral number of octets (Alignment Error).

h3cEOCUniInUndersizePkts.name: h3cEOCUniInUndersizePkts
h3cEOCUniInUndersizePkts.description: The total number of packets received that are less than 64 octets long (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and are otherwise well formed.

h3cEOCUniInOversizePkts.name: h3cEOCUniInOversizePkts
h3cEOCUniInOversizePkts.description: The total number of packets received that are longer than 1518 octets (excluding framing bits, but including FCS octets) and are otherwise well formed.

h3cEOCUniInErrorbyOther.name: h3cEOCUniInErrorbyOther
h3cEOCUniInErrorbyOther.description: The total number of other error packets received on this interface.

h3cEOCUniInOctets.name: h3cEOCUniInOctets
h3cEOCUniInOctets.description: The total number of octets received on this interface.

h3cEOCUniOutPkts.name: h3cEOCUniOutPkts
h3cEOCUniOutPkts.description: The total number of packets (including bad packets, broadcast packets, and multicast packets) sent.

h3cEOCUniOutUPkts.name: h3cEOCUniOutUPkts
h3cEOCUniOutUPkts.description: The total number of good packets sent that are directed to the unicast address. Note that this does not include multicast and broadcast packets.

h3cEOCUniOutBPkts.name: h3cEOCUniOutBPkts
h3cEOCUniOutBPkts.description: The total number of good packets sent that are directed to the broadcast address. Note that this does not include multicast packets.

h3cEOCUniOutMPkts.name: h3cEOCUniOutMPkts
h3cEOCUniOutMPkts.description: The total number of good packets sent that are directed to a multicast address. Note that this number does not include packets directed to the broadcast address.

h3cEOCUniOutPausePkts.name: h3cEOCUniOutPausePkts
h3cEOCUniOutPausePkts.description: The total number of MAC control packets sent on this interface by the pause operation. This counter does not increment when the interface is in a half-duplex mode. Discontinuities in the value of this counter can occur at re-initialization of the management system.

h3cEOCUniOutTotalErrors.name: h3cEOCUniOutTotalErrors
h3cEOCUniOutTotalErrors.description: The total number of error packets sent on this interface.

h3cEOCUniOutCollisions.name: h3cEOCUniOutCollisions
h3cEOCUniOutCollisions.description: The best estimate of the total number of collisions on this Ethernet segment. The value returned will depend on the location of the RMON probe. Section 8.2.1.3 (10BASE-5) and section 10.3.1.3 (10BASE-2) of IEEE standard 802.3 states that a station must detect a collision, in the receive mode, if three or more stations are transmitting simultaneously. A repeater port must detect a collision when two or more stations are transmitting simultaneously. Thus a probe placed on a repeater port could record more collisions than a probe connected to a station on the same segment could. Probe location plays a much smaller role when considering 10BASE-T. 14.2.1.4 (10BASE-T) of IEEE standard 802.3 defines a collision as the simultaneous presence of signals on the DO and RD circuits (transmitting and receiving at the same time). A 10BASE-T station can only detect collisions when it is transmitting. Thus probes placed on a station and a repeater, should report the same number of collisions. Note also that an RMON probe inside a repeater should ideally report collisions between the repeater and one or more other hosts (transmit collisions as defined by IEEE 802.3k) plus receiver collisions observed on any coax segments to which the repeater is connected.

h3cEOCUniOutDelayExceedDsds.name: h3cEOCUniOutDelayExceedDsds
h3cEOCUniOutDelayExceedDsds.description: The number of packets discarded by this port due to excessive transit delay through the bridge. It is incremented by both transparent and source route bridges.

h3cEOCUniOutErrorbyOther.name: h3cEOCUniOutErrorbyOther
h3cEOCUniOutErrorbyOther.description: The total number of other error packets sent on this interface. Other error packets means the error packets out of collision packets and excessive delayed packets.

h3cEOCUniOutDroppedFrames.name: h3cEOCUniOutDroppedFrames
h3cEOCUniOutDroppedFrames.description: The total number of frames dropped because of buffer failure.

h3cEOCUniOutOctets.name: h3cEOCUniOutOctets
h3cEOCUniOutOctets.description: The total number of octets transmitted out of the interface.

h3cEOCCnuRegExcessTrap.name: h3cEOCCnuRegExcessTrap
h3cEOCCnuRegExcessTrap.description: A h3cEOCCnuRegExcessTrap notification is sent when the number of registered CNUs exceeds the limit.

h3cEOCCnuRegExcessRecoverTrap.name: h3cEOCCnuRegExcessRecoverTrap
h3cEOCCnuRegExcessRecoverTrap.description: A h3cEOCCnuRegExcessRecoverTrap notification is sent when h3cEOCCnuRegExcessTrap is detected and then recoverd.

h3cEOCCnuRegSuccTrap.name: h3cEOCCnuRegSuccTrap
h3cEOCCnuRegSuccTrap.description: A h3cEOCCnuRegSuccTrap notification is sent when a CNU registers successful.

h3cEOCCnuOffLineTrap.name: h3cEOCCnuOffLineTrap
h3cEOCCnuOffLineTrap.description: A h3cEOCCnuOffLineTrap notification is sent when a CNU offline.

h3cEOCCnuLinkupTrap.name: h3cEOCCnuLinkupTrap
h3cEOCCnuLinkupTrap.description: A h3cEOCCnuLinkupTrap notification is sent when a CNU linkup.

h3cEOCOamDisconnectTrap.name: h3cEOCOamDisconnectTrap
h3cEOCOamDisconnectTrap.description: A h3cEOCOamDisconnectionTrap notification is sent when LLID's OAM link is disconnected.

h3cEOCOamDisconnectRecoverTrap.name: h3cEOCOamDisconnectRecoverTrap
h3cEOCOamDisconnectRecoverTrap.description: A h3cEOCOamDisconnectionRecoverTrap notification is sent when LLID's OAM link is disconnected and then connected.

h3cEOCBandwidthNotEnoughTrap.name: h3cEOCBandwidthNotEnoughTrap
h3cEOCBandwidthNotEnoughTrap.description: Bandwidth is not enough, cnu can not bind now.

h3cEOCCnuAttenuationTrap.name: h3cEOCCnuAttenuationTrap
h3cEOCCnuAttenuationTrap.description: A h3cHPEOCCnuAttenuationTrap notification is sent when a CNU's attenuation is changing.

h3cEOCCnuRegFailTrap.name: h3cEOCCnuRegFailTrap
h3cEOCCnuRegFailTrap.description: A h3cEOCCnuRegFailTrap notification is sent when a CNU registers fail.

h3cEOCCLTCablePortErrorTrap.name: h3cEOCCLTCablePortErrorTrap
h3cEOCCLTCablePortErrorTrap.description: A h3cEOCCLTCablePortErrorTrap notification is sent when the hardware of cable port occurs error or CLT's vlan is configged error.

h3cEOCCLTCablePortErrReTrap.name: h3cEOCCLTCablePortErrReTrap
h3cEOCCLTCablePortErrReTrap.description: A h3cEOCCLTCablePortErrReTrap notification is sent when cable port error and then recovered.

h3cEOCCnuTxRateDropTrap.name: h3cEOCCnuTxRateDropTrap
h3cEOCCnuTxRateDropTrap.description: A h3cEOCCnuTxRateDropTrap notification is sent when cable port rate of TX capability drop exceeded threshold.

h3cEOCCnuTxRateDropRecoverTrap.name: h3cEOCCnuTxRateDropRecoverTrap
h3cEOCCnuTxRateDropRecoverTrap.description: A h3cEOCCnuTxRateDropRecoverTrap notification is sent when cable port rate of TX capability recover from the recent rate-drop trap.

h3cEOCCnuRxRateDropTrap.name: h3cEOCCnuRxRateDropTrap
h3cEOCCnuRxRateDropTrap.description: A h3cEOCCnuRxRateDropTrap notification is sent when cable port rate of RX capability drop exceeded threshold.

h3cEOCCnuRxRateDropRecoverTrap.name: h3cEOCCnuRxRateDropRecoverTrap
h3cEOCCnuRxRateDropRecoverTrap.description: A h3cEOCCnuRxRateDropRecoverTrap notification is sent when cable port rate of RX capability recover from the recent rate-drop trap.

h3cEOCCnuFWDownLoadErrTrap.name: h3cEOCCnuFWDownLoadErrTrap
h3cEOCCnuFWDownLoadErrTrap.description: A h3cEOCCnuFWDownLoadErrTrap notification is sent when CLT can't download CNU firmware from the server successfully.

h3cEOCCnuFWDownLoadErrReTrap.name: h3cEOCCnuFWDownLoadErrReTrap
h3cEOCCnuFWDownLoadErrReTrap.description: A h3cEOCCnuFWDownLoadErrReTrap notification is sent when CLT recover from the download CNU firmware error.
